=== Seizure-Like Episodes
<subsec:seizures>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Episodes resembling seizures but with normal EEG (non-epileptic)
    - Triggered by sensory overload, exertion, or stress
    - May include loss of motor control, altered consciousness, or convulsive movements
    - Distinct from true epilepsy

*Mechanism.*
Non-epileptic seizure-like episodes may reflect severe autonomic dysfunction, cerebral hypoperfusion, or metabolic crisis in brain tissue.
